PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)
Project: Hybrid Programmable Bag
1. Product Overview
1.1 Product Name

Hybrid Programmable Bag

1.2 Product Type

Interactive fashion-tech prototype (physical + digital hybrid system)

1.3 Product Vision

Hybrid Programmable Bag is a 3D-printed sculptural object that merges physical form with programmable digital identity.

The project explores how a physical object can become dynamically customizable through artificial intelligence and real-time web-based interaction.

The bag becomes:

A programmable surface
A hybrid design object
A digitally-extended physical artifact

2. Product Goals
2.1 Primary Goals

Transform a static physical object into a programmable system

Enable real-time interaction between web interface and hardware

Integrate AI-generated visuals into tangible materiality

Create a fully functional prototype

2.2 Success Criteria

The project is successful when:

AI-generated textures can be created via prompt input

Generated images appear on the bag’s screen

LED lighting can be adjusted in real time

Servo motors can be triggered via the website

Communication between website and bag is stable and responsive (<2 seconds latency)

